# **How Reliable Are Weather Forecasts?** {style="text-align: center; color: green"}

![](images/forecast-reliability.jpg){fig-align="center" width="457"}

## Dataset {style="text-align: center"}

The dataset Weather_forecast_Accuracy includes 16 months of forecasts and observations from 167 cities. Weather_forecast_Accuracy is divided into three dimensions, `weather_forecasts`, `cities`, and `outlook_meanings`.

## Question 1: How does the error in temperature prediction vary across the United States? And can we identify clusters of cities with similar error patterns? {style="text-align: center"}

